@PresidencyZA @DMRE_ZA @NationalTreasury @CEF_ZA @SFF_ZA
@CyrilRamaphosa 
@ParliamentofRSA @GovernmentZA and every minister and department complicit in this mess - Mineral Resources & Petroleum/Energy @DMPR_ZA @GwedeMantashe1 Finance/National Treasury @TreasuryRSA @DrDavidMasondo and the Central Energy Fund/Strategic Fuel Fund @SACentralEnerg1 :

Your repeated above-inflation (and cumulative) hikes on non-crude elements - general fuel levy, RAF levy, margins and other administered add-ons - have grossly exacerbated fuel prices for many years. The graph proves it: petrol prices decoupled and over-recovered relative to Brent crude in ZAR since ~2015, while the crude-driven component became a smaller share. How do you expect the economy to grow when transport costs inflate everything or when the poor majority - reliant on taxis, buses, and cheap food - are forced to bear this stealth tax burden that hits them hardest?

When was the last proper, independent public audit of the fuel reserve fund and these non-crude levies? Why have our strategic reserves never recovered from the dodgy 2015 sale under then-Energy Minister Tina Joemat-Pettersson - a transaction the Auditor-General later found illegal for lacking Finance Minister approval and fetching far less than claimed? Why are we still sitting at only ~8 million barrels (woefully inadequate for real shocks) while pushing new policies for 60+ days that should have been fixed long ago?

Why have we abandoned refining the bulk of our own fuel? Multiple major refineries closed or mothballed under your watch and predecessors, forcing ~60-75%+ import dependence (even higher for diesel). The apartheid regime - despite heavy sanctions and isolation - built and maintained far greater self-sufficiency through Sasol and domestic capacity. Now we’re exposed to every global price spike and supply disruption while paying premiums on imports.

Reality Check: Comparing 1994 to the current 2026 coastal price (~R25.23/L for petrol), the nominal price has obscenely increased by over 1 350%! It’s no overstatement to say that ANC governance has been a scourge on our nation. 

Stop pretending this is just “market forces” or “global oil.” The non-crude wedge, failed reserves management and collapsed refining are policy choices with your fingerprints all over them. The poor are paying the price while the economy stagnates. 

Fix it or step aside for people who will. South Africans deserve better than this ongoing failure on energy security and affordability. Stop your Superglue ANC iron-fisted grip on the GNU and appoint non cadres who are the best experts in their fields to head up the relevant government departments to correct this hot mess. 😡
